{"type": "item.completed", "item": {"id": "item_3", "type": "command_execution", "command": "/bin/zsh -lc \"sed -n '1,260p' ../../public/task_board.md\"", "aggregated_output": "# Task Board\n\n## Directions (Long-term Goals - Set by Lord Only)\n| ID | Title | Description | Priority | Group | Assignee | Status | Created | Updated | Notes |\n|----|-------|-------------|----------|-------|----------|--------|---------|---------|-------|\n| D001 | Build profitable Kalshi trading operation | Trade on Kalshi.com prediction markets \u2014 find edge, build models, make money | high | all | undefined | open | 2026-04-02 | 2026-04-02 | kalshi.com \u2014 CFTC-regulated prediction market exchange |\n| D002 | Develop data-driven trading strategies | Identify market mispricings vs real-world probability across econ, politics, crypto, weather | high | all | undefined | open | 2026-04-02 | 2026-04-02 | API docs: trading-api.readme.io/reference/getting-started |\n| D003 | Track P&L and iterate fast | Define position sizing rules, measure strategy performance, kill losers, scale winners | high | all | undefined | open | 2026-04-02 | 2026-04-02 | Start with paper trading, then real capital |\n| D004 | Build Kalshi Arbitrage Engine (Wen Zhou) | **PHASE 1: Market Filtering (Daily Scan).** Filter Kalshi markets by: (1) Volume \u226510,000 (exclude low-liquidity noise), (2) YES/NO ratio targets: 15-30% or 70-85% (mispriced range). Reject middle 40-60% (too efficient, no edge). Reject extremes 0-15% & 85-100% (distorted pricing). Rationale: Extreme ratios have unrealistic implied probabilities; middle range reflects consensus (no inefficiency). Output: filtered market list for Phase 2. **PHASE 2: LLM-Based Clustering (Daily Scan).** Use LLM embeddings to identify hidden market correlations. Group similar markets (e.g., Bitcoin $100k + Ethereum $5k + Crypto dominance all cluster together). Find markets with strong semantic/causal links that traditional screening misses. Output: market clusters for Phase 3. **PHASE 3: Pearson Pairwise Correlation Detection (Daily Scan).** Apply Pearson/distance-based algorithm (ref: hudson-and-thames-arbitragelab) to detect strongly correlated market pairs. Identify mispricings: if BTC moves +5% in backtest but only +2% in live, that's arbitrage. Calculate expected spread from historical correlation. Score confidence. Output: correlation_pairs.json with arbitrage candidates. **PHASE 4: C++ High-Frequency Execution (Real-Time).** Why C++: Each trade moves prices; we need sub-millisecond execution to capture arbitrage before it reverts. Algorithm: (1) Detect spread gap between correlated markets, (2) Calculate theoretical fair spread, (3) Execute buy/sell pairs to lock profit, (4) Monitor until convergence. No Python delays. No GIL. Pure performance. **Why This Works:** Phases 1-3 reduce noise (99% of markets ignored), find real edges via correlation-based pairs (harder to game than single-market signals), Phase 4 captures spread before reversion. This is the real edge. Reference: https://hudson-and-thames-arbitragelab.readthedocs-hosted.com/en/latest/distance_approach/pearson_approach.html | high | all | undefined | open | 2026-04-03 | 2026-04-03 | Wen Zhou strategy \u2014 full 4-phase pipeline. Phases 1-3 = daily batch. Phase 4 = real-time. Blocks live trading pending T236 (API credentials). |\n| D005 | Continuously improve the platform, pipeline quality, and agent collaboration | Agents should proactively find bugs, improve code quality, optimize token usage, evolve personas, and strengthen culture. Every agent is responsible for making the whole system better, not just their own tasks. | high | all |  | open | 2026-04-04 | 2026-04-04 |  |\n\n## Instructions (Persistent Context - Always Consider)\n| ID | Title | Description | Priority | Group | Assignee | Status | Created | Updated | Notes |\n|----|-------|-------------|----------|-------|----------|--------|---------|---------|-------|\n| I001 | Token-efficient ops: grep tasks, avoid full-file reads | undefined | undefined | all | undefined | open | undefined | undefined | See CLAUDE.md |\n\n## Tasks (Regular Work - Assignable & Completable)\n| ID | Title | Description | Priority | Group | Assignee | Status | Created | Updated | Notes |\n|----|-------|-------------|----------|-------|----------|--------|---------|---------|-------|\n| 714 | Per-trade stop-loss: prevent single trade exceeding max loss | Add stop-loss logic to the paper trading simulation (output/pipeline_report). Tina flagged this during Sprint 4 QA. No single trade should exceed 20% of capital. See output/dave/pipeline_report.md for current simulation. | high | all | dave | open | 2026-04-07 | 2026-04-07 |  |\n| 715 | Post-trade capital floor: halt trading if capital drops below $50 | Add capital floor check to the simulation engine. If capital drops below $50 threshold, halt trading and report. See agents/bob/output/signal_generator.js for the current signal logic. | high | all | bob | open | 2026-04-07 | 2026-04-07 |  |\n| 716 | Rate limit integration test with realistic API load | Verify the Kalshi API rate limiter works correctly under load. Write a test that fires 50+ requests and validates rate limiting behavior. Part of production hardening before live API use. | medium | all | bob | open | 2026-04-07 | 2026-04-07 |  |\n| 717 | Sprint 5 velocity tracking setup | Set up velocity tracking for Sprint 5. Track task completion rates, cycle health, and flag blockers early. Report to alice each sprint day. | medium | all | sam | open | 2026-04-07 | 2026-04-07 |  |\n", "exit_code": 0, "status": "completed"}}
